Prepare for big cheesy grins at your dinner table tonight! You'll season our grilling cheese with Tuscan Heat Spice, then sear it in a pan and watch as it crisps on the outside, while turning wonderfully melty on the inside. For even more dinnertime delight, you'll top the cheese with a Sicilian-inspired relish, featuring walnuts, parsley, tomato, and raisins. It's all served over fragrant jasmine rice and drizzled with balsamic glaze for a fab finish. Say (grilling) cheese!

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, @Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2%tsp}, and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook, covered, until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Halve, peel, and mince half the @shallot{1}. Finely dice @tomato{1}. Pick @parsley{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves. Roughly chop @walnuts{1/2%oz}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine garlic and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Microwave on high until fragrant, ~{45%seconds}.

Add shallot, tomato, parsley, walnuts, @golden raisins{1%oz}, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season relish with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Slice @grilling cheese{6%oz} lengthwise into 6 pieces. Brush all over with a drizzle of oil. Place remaining @Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2%tbsp} on a #plate{}; press cheese into spice, coating both sides. (It's OK if not all the spice sticks.)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add seasoned grilling cheese and cook until golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, if desired.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with grilling cheese and relish. Drizzle with as much @balsamic glaze{5%tsp} as you like. Serve with a squeeze of lemon juice.

> The Sicilian-inspired relish adds a wonderful balance to the spiciness of the Tuscan Heat Spice and richness of the grilling cheese.